voice_to_text: okay I guess it's my time to shine so there's a big difference between not wanting to be a parent and not wanting to be pregnant and that's the weird camp that I fall into personally I absolutely want to be a parent um I did not want to be when I was younger um but I the idea of being pregnant is just so viscerally horrifying to me part of that has to do with gender reasons I have a lot of um dysphoria around the idea of pregnancy I also have a lot of dysphoria around my menstrual cycle don't like it I really don't like having any sort of physical reminder of my assigned seggs I guess but a lot of that also has to do with the fact that I have a collection of menagerie if you will of various chronic conditions that would make carrying a healthy baby to term very difficult or possibly unalive both me and said baby so I got my first IUD when I was 15 for symptoms um relating to my period that were very very red flaggy but nobody cared to diagnose me with PCOS at the time was not even seggsually active but was just in so much pain that I needed to be on birth control got my second one right after and then as soon as that expired I was just like what are we what are we doing here so I got surgically sterilized at the age of 28 I don't regret it I don't think I ever will regret it um there's something not just horrifying in a weird body horror dysphoria way for me personally about pregnancy but also just I cannot fathom getting pregnant and trying to carry a baby to term and losing my baby or losing my own life because of something I was aware that was wrong with me before I got pregnant and that's not me gatekeeping pregnancy plenty of disabled and chronically ill people can and do carry healthy babies to term I'm not one of them if the opportunity presents itself for me to become a step parent or a foster parent or adopt then great um but I I don't regret getting sterilized young at all
